<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Normandy</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-13 14:44:53</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>No, this is quite useful, especially in groups.<BR>
<BR>
If you've lost track of a group member, or vice versa, target him (via your Group List), and then fire Flare.  The flare will curve around and fly right at him.  You can follow the flare to him, and/or he can watch to see where the flare comes from and trace it back to its source.<BR>
<BR>
Likewise, if you lose track of a monster you have targeted, fire a flare and follow it to the monster.<BR>
<BR>
This is handy because the flare's "guidance mechanism" can track a group member far farther than AutoFollow can.<BR>
<BR>
And if a group member is entirely out of range, just untarget and then fire the flare straight ahead.  It's visible for quite a distance, and your group member can watch for it.  In tough cases, fire a flare, turn right 45 degrees, fire another, and so on, firing a flare in every direction.  You're bound to shoot one across the bow of a group member who can then follow it backwards to where you are.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
